What is the meaning of the proverb “necessity is the mother of invention”? The author of this proverb is unknown but, it has been stated over and over throughout history. This proverb sort of means, that if there is a need, there is an invention. Maybe, the first invention used by homo sapiens was the sharpened stick used as a tool to gather food and as a weapon. The greatest invention in time had to be the handcrafted flint knife two and half million years ago.
Humans have made countless inventions that have made us what we are today. The inventions of items such as clay pots, wooden tools, flint and stone tools, copper, bronze, and iron tools have had the greatest impact on human lives. These tools have made it possible to create other items such as the wheel, canoe, and countless types of homes and other structures.
Through time things change, items come and go, steam passed on to the petrol engine, the buggy wipe passed on to the throttle. One item makes way for another, each builds on to the next. Connections through history, we learn what works and what doesn’t. Like nature, we evolve in our daily lives, looking forward, designing, creating, developing, improving, improvising, and finding what we need and want to make our lives better.
If I had to guess, I would say there are as many inventions as there are days in history. Today we are again faced with reinventing the wheel. People must survive, they must get on with their lives, we must carry forward the meaning of, do your best to get the most. People must be empowered to do their best again in new ways. We will find new ways to do things, new ways to refill our lives with our needs, new ways to meet and greet, and new ways to overcome our fears.
The human need to survive is great, the demand to get ahead and be successful is so strong that people die in their efforts to achieve their goals. Inventions go hand and hand for these efforts. Humans will go forward learning as they go again to see what works and what doesn’t, all facing risk of failure or of success. In all of time humans survive and overcome those failures. Often these successes give humans far better lives than before the difficulties and challenges they faced. The ability of the human to adapt to new difficulties is most impressive. Every success has always driven humans to advance to other goals and greater things. These goals have humans climb the mountains, to cross the seas, to take flight, and fly to the moon. We are all dreamers we all want what is best and this gives way to “necessity is the mother of invention”.
We, The People will restart our lives. We must be patient, have hope, have faith in yourself, in your family, in your neighbors and we will survive together so, look ahead towards a new life. The hope is for a better life, one where you can say we did it with pride. When your grandchildren read your story, they will smile and say yes, and look how well my life is today.
